				<td colspan="2"><span>Theres a lot of factors The ground your standing on, whether or not your lev'd(levitated circles ARE smaller, played with it the other day), lag. Without seeing you in action I really can't tell what your doing wrong.
<br />

<br />
For me, when I auto-circle, all I have up is  lvl 49 selos. I use my rujarkian lute in main hand and epic in offhand but the mod levels are nearly identical(I'm about 2% off from TDoK selos). 
<br />

<br />
A nice safe place to check if your circles are the right size would be the guards at West Freeport. Just pull one with a slow or something and drag it out to the middle of the newbie area. Plenty of room to try out auto-circling, the ground is flat, just find a place without cacti, guards wont be able to kill you. Qeynos works as well, just avoid killing them if you dont want to mess with your faction.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
